They were unable to travel to perform the normal body tuning process in Japan, so there are ongoing requests and updates being processed. For example Gura's tail and her shoulders have improved by a lot. Ame has been getting more physics but they didn't have collision sorted out in time for the recording. This event was not able to use the studio in Japan, so they had to record motion data and produce composite animations. Kanauru was brought in to clean up the motion data, supply additional animations and composite the final 3D. All of the 3D portion of the event was a series of recordings rendered in Kanauru's animation software, that's why it has his style of shaders. Unless maybe Amelia or someone else inside Hololive needed to import Kanauru's scene data and try to add the official 3D models themselves......it really depends whether Cover allowed an outside contractor to access the model data. This was literally the first time anyone in Hololive did things this way, due to not being able to use the normal studio assets.

There's no way the VRchat engine could handle anything like this, last I checked.
